name: Nantucket Health & Human Services Dept
tweet: Currently, there is no confirmation of a new COVID variant on Nantucket. We are investigating the possible presence of the South African variant B1.3.5.1 and the P.1 Brazilian variant. Sorry for any confusion an early email that originated in this office may have caused.

name: Nantucket Health & Human Services Dept
tweet: @loisromano @TownofNantucket @MassDPH @EdMarkey @USRepKeating @SenWarren @MassGovernor Hi Lois. Sorry for the confusion. There NO NEW VARIANT of covid on island. We are sending a clarifying email now. Thank you for your concern

name: Nantucket Health & Human Services Dept
tweet: There are still no cases of #COVID19 on Nantucket. While risk of contracting this virus remains low, it is important that we all practice healthy habits. If you suspect you may have symptoms of #COVID19 (dry cough, fever, shortness of breath), call your doctor or @ACKHospital

name: Nantucket Health & Human Services Dept
tweet: With Spring approaching, we expect to see an ⬆️ in our tick population. Did you know tick borne illness accounted for 93% of all infectious disease on Nantucket from 2009-2018? Check out our Infectious Disease Report.   https://t.co/rbOXseXnxK

name: Nantucket Health & Human Services Dept
tweet: #COVID19 is a constantly developing epidemic. In addition to practicing healthy habits like washing you hands and covering your cough, it's also important to stay informed. Stay up-to-date with #COVID19 using this map developed by @JohnsHopkinsSPH  https://t.co/2PrA0bDveW
